# Rhino Player ‚Äî Cursor / agent context (compact)

## Purpose

- **Rhino Player**: mpv-backed media player for Linux (GNOME, Ubuntu, and similar) with **GTK4 / libadwaita** UI, implemented in **Rust**, targeting a **statically linked** distributable when feasible.
- **Product context**: `docs/product-and-use-cases.md` (use cases and feature map). Behavior is specified in `docs/` first, then implemented. Copyright (C) 2026 Peter Adrianov; license `GPL-3.0-or-later` in root `LICENSE` / `COPYRIGHT` and the About dialog.

## Directories

- `build.rs` ‚Äî Linux: embeds `DT_RUNPATH` for `/usr/local/lib/<multiarch>` and `/usr/local/lib` so a locally built `libmpv` (e.g. VapourSynth) is preferred over the distro copy without `LD_LIBRARY_PATH`.
- `data/` ‚Äî Freedesktop assets: `data/icons` (hicolor, `source/*` design + `rebuild-png-assets.sh`; see `data/icons/README.md`), `data/vs` (bundled full-affinity `rhino_60_mvtools.vpy`, `libmvtools.so` path cached in settings + `RHINO_MVTOOLS_LIB`; [VapourSynth](https://www.vapoursynth.com/) notes: `data/vs/README.md`), `data/applications/*.desktop`, `data/metainfo` (AppStream), `install-to-user-dirs.sh` (installs to `~/.local/share` for shell/taskbar icon). Index: `data/README.md`.
- `docs/` ‚Äî Feature specs **before** implementation. Index: `docs/README.md`. One file per feature area under `docs/features/`. Product and use cases: `docs/product-and-use-cases.md`.
- `src/` ‚Äî `main.rs` (entry + locale), `lib.rs`, `sched.rs` (Linux `ioprio_set` I/O *class* best-effort at startup‚Äîno `nice`; from `main` before GTK), `app.rs` (GTK shell, `GtkWindowHandle` on `ToolbarView` content for move-from-video, `APP_ID`, bottom-bar prev/play/next + seek + times + **Close video** (`app.close-video`), header speed popover (`speedometer-symbolic`) + sound popover: volume + audio tracks + main menu **Open** / **Move to Trash** (local file) / **Preferences** ‚Üí **Smooth video (~60 FPS at 1.0√ó)** (VapourSynth) + script picker, `db::init` on startup, `eof-reached` ‚Üí `sibling_advance`), `audio_tracks.rs` (mpv `track-list` + `aid`, radio list in sound popover), `icons.rs` (hicolor search path for `cargo run`), `db.rs` (SQLite `rhino.sqlite`: history, `settings` kv: `video_smooth_60` / `video_vs_path` / `video_mvtools_lib`, media duration/thumbs), `video_pref.rs` (normal playback leaves mpv defaults; optional VapourSynth `vf` from `db::VideoPrefs`, bundled `data/vs/rhino_60_mvtools.vpy`, mvtools cache + `RHINO_MVTOOLS_LIB` from `paths::mvtools_from_env` / `mvtools_lib_search`), `mpv_embed.rs` (libmpv `RenderContext` + `GLArea`, default mpv timing headroom, no optional `report_swap`, `apply_mpv_video` after init, `commit_quit`), `idle_inhibit.rs` (GTK `Application::inhibit` IDLE+SUSPEND when playing, recent grid hidden; clear on quit), `paths.rs` (XDG config, mpv `watch_later`, bundled `.vpy`, mvtools discovery), `history.rs` (recent list via `db`), `media_probe.rs` (`remove_continue_entry` = resume clear + history remove, card data, libmpv `vo=image` + quit thumb for DB), `seek_bar_preview.rs` (popover + time; 2nd libmpv + small `GLArea` / `MpvPreviewGl` like the main [embed]), `jpeg_texture.rs` (JPEG ‚Üí `GdkTexture` for recent grid; not `Texture::from_bytes` for raw bytes), `continue_undo.rs` (session snackbar **Undo**: list-remove vs **trash** + untrash), `trash_xdg.rs` (Freedesktop `Trash` locate + restore from `files/`), `sibling_advance.rs` (next/prev local file in folder + sibling order; EOF + bottom bar), `video_ext.rs` (shared `SUFFIX` list for **Open** dialog + `sibling_advance` folder scan), `recent_view.rs` (continue grid, card hover: **trash** + **remove**, spacer `dbl`‚Üífullscreen, session undo), `time.rs` (time formatting + tests), `playback_speed.rs` (1.0/1.5/2.0√ó + mpv `speed` sync for header `ListBox`), `theme.rs` (CSS: dark chrome + `cursor: pointer` / `not-allowed` on controls; see `.cursor/rules/ui-cursor.mdc`).
- `tests/` ‚Äî Integration tests (e.g. libmpv smoke).

## Workflow

- **Document-first**: see `.cursor/rules/document-first.mdc`. Do not implement substantial features without an up-to-date `docs/features/‚Ä¶` file (status, short/long description, specification).
- **Known UX not achieved in testing (Composer 2 Fast pass):** one-click switch between header `MenuButton` popovers; Prev/Next filename tooltips ‚Äî see `docs/README.md` (*Tooling note*) and `docs/features/17-window-behavior.md` / `07-sibling-folder-queue.md`. Revisit with a different model or deeper GTK review.

## Conventions

- Keep `.cursorrules` and `docs/README.md` feature list aligned with what exists in the tree.
- Prefer clear module boundaries: UI (GTK/Adwaita), mpv control, platform (DBus, portals), persistence (settings, session).
- **Clippy:** run `cargo qcheck` (or `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features`); do not add `#[allow(clippy::‚Ä¶)]`‚Äîfix by refactoring (see `.cursor/rules/clippy-no-suppress.mdc`).
- **Complexity and module shape:** there is no Ruby-style `AbcSize` in Rust; use Clippy (see `clippy.toml`, `cargo qcheck`: cognitive complexity + `too_many_lines` for functions) and follow `.cursor/rules/complexity-and-module-design.mdc` (if a feature touches **>6 files** or a module grows past **1000 lines**, refactor toward SOLID / single reason to change per module; Clippy does not enforce whole-file length).
- **UI / IO timing:** prefer event subscriptions over periodic polls; see `.cursor/rules/events-over-polling.mdc`.
- Name length: prefer short, clear identifiers (2‚Äì3 words) for new types and functions, consistent with the rest of the file.
